[User]: I just installed a proxmox cluster with 2 nodes. Configure the proxmox cluster and prepare it to deploy a k8s cluster with multiple nodes. The k8s cluster should optimize all resource that is has on the proxmox cluster. The k8s should be a HA cluster, with an ingress controller and a hello world application. The ingress cluster should be accesible from the local network on port 80 and 443.
[Architect_Zero]: 

**High-level architecture plan:**

- Deploy Kubernetes (e.g. via `kubeadm` or containerized control plane) on your two Proxmox nodes, ensuring at least one control plane node per availability zone. Use network policies to segment control plane ↔ workers and enforce least privilege.
- Create dedicated worker nodes from the remaining Proxmox hosts. Configure pod networking (e.g. Calico or Cilium) with network policies to restrict pod-to-pod traffic.
- Set up an ingress controller (e.g. Nginx Ingress) on the control plane to manage external access (ports 80/443). Restrict ingress binding to specific host networks and apply TLS termination. For local network accessibility, ensure firewall rules allow traffic to the ingress IP/port range on your local subnet.
- Deploy a minimal “hello-world” application (e.g. an Nginx static page deployment) as a test workload to validate networking and ingress routing.
- Optimize resource utilization with:
  - Horizontal/Vertical Pod Autoscaling based on CPU, memory, or custom metrics.
  - Node autoscaling groups/policies if spanning multiple physical hosts.
  - Appropriate storage classes for Proxmox volumes tied to node affinity/anti-affinity.
  - Resource quotas and limit ranges per namespace.

**Next steps:**
- @Security_Sentinel: Review this topology and ingress configuration for any exposed surfaces or overly permissive rules before proceeding.
